reviews.text: Absolutly outraged would be an understatment.I arrived the day after my train and it had already left!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! blood riduclous kids these days have no manners *eye roll emoji*

Standard Greater Anglia main line facilities, such as toilets, waiting room, and small coffee shop, however on Sundays I don't really think the station caters to travellers very well, because the changeover times are much longer on Sundays and I'm pretty sure the the café isn't open for long or at all
Today just changing trains, but know the place well... Worth to stop and have a good time..

I've been catching the train here all my life the people who work here are friendly, yes the shop closes at 5 but that's so they can go home to their families. There are 2 waiting rooms one on each platform and a ticket machine on both as well.
An attractive traditional railway station on the Great Eastern Main Line. Class 90 hauled passenger trains pass through daily.
